The paper discusses distributed machine learning algorithms, particularly those based on stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and its variants. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a fast distributed asynchronous SGD-based algorithm with variance reduction, which involves optimization techniques and distributed computing, indicating that it could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also mentions experiments on the Google Cloud Computing Platform, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions solution quality, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
